ntinued in regular use to the present day.  Roger, Count of Sicily  (  <i>c.</i>1031–1101 ), son of Tancred, recovered Sicily from the Arabs. His son, also called Roger, ruled Sicily as king, presiding over a court noted for its splendour and patronage of the arts."],"variants":[{"name":"Rodger","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Roger  , in part from the surname derived from the given name in the Middle Ages."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Roger d'Apleby was born about 1196, in Buglawton, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Mrs. Roger D\"Apleby. He died about 1242, in Milton Keynes, Buckinghamshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 48."},"et":{"about 1196–about 1242":"umbes 1196–umbes 1242","1197–Female":"1197–Surnud","1220–1250":"1220–1250","1222–1246":"1222–1246","1196–1242":"1196–1242","1246":"1246","1222":"1222","1220":"1220","1242":"1242","1197":"1197","1196":"1196","1250":"1250","about 1242":"umbes 1242","about 1196":"umbes 1196","Buglawton, Cheshire, England":"Buglawton, Cheshire, England","Milton Keynes, Buckinghamshire, England, United Kingdom":"Milton Keynes, Buckinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Buglawton, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom":"Buglawton, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Appleby Magna, Leicestershire, England":"Appleby Magna, Leicestershire, England"},"fi":{"about 1196–about 1242":"noin 1196–noin 1242","1197–Female":"1197–Kuollut","1220–1250":"1220–1250","1222–1246":"1222–1246","1196–1242":"1196–1242","1246":"1246","1222":"1222","1220":"1220","1242":"1242","1197":"1197","1196":"1196","1250":"1250","about 1242":"noin 1242","about 1196":"noin 1196","Buglawton, Cheshire, England":"Buglawton, Cheshire, England","Milton Keynes, Buckinghamshire, England, United Kingdom":"Milton Keynes, Buckinghamshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Buglawton, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom":"Buglawton, Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Appleby Magna, Leicestershire, England":"Appleby Magna, L